        "title": "docs: add MegaBrain Gateway (OpenAI-compatible) to model providers",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Adds **MegaBrain Gateway** as a custom/base-URL provider in `docs/concepts/model-providers.md`\n- MegaBrain is an OpenAI-compatible gateway with 500+ models across 60+ providers and `mb-auto/*` auto-routing models\n- Placed in the `## Providers via models.providers (custom/base URL)` section alongside Moonshot, Volcano Engine, and other OpenAI-compatible proxies — consistent format with those entries\n\n## Config example added\n\n```json5\n{\n  agents: {\n    defaults: { model: { primary: \"megabrain/mb-auto/balanced\" } },\n  },\n  models: {\n    mode: \"merge\",\n    providers: {\n      megabrain: {\n        baseUrl: \"https://getmegabrain.com/api/gateway/v1\",\n        apiKey: \"${MEGABRAIN_API_KEY}\",\n        api: \"openai-completions\",\n        models: [\n          { id: \"mb-auto/balanced\", name: \"MB Auto Balanced\" },\n          { id: \"mb-auto/frontier\", name: \"MB Auto Frontier\" },\n        ],\n      },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [ ] Verify the new section renders correctly in docs\n- [ ] Confirm `baseUrl` endpoint returns OpenAI-compatible responses at `/chat/completions`\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
